080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEyODYyMDY0Mjg3NDkxNzEy/2025-honda-cr-v-sport-touring-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEyODYyMDY0Mjg3NDkxNzEy/2025-honda-cr-v-sport-touring-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEyODYyMDY0Mjg3NDkxNzEy/2025-honda-cr-v-sport-touring-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEyODYyMDY0Mjg3NDkxNzEy/2025-honda-cr-v-sport-touring-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/MjEyODYyMDY0Mjg3NDkxNzEy/2025-honda-cr-v-sport-touring-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330-880330.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"the-2025-honda-cr-v-is-a-balanced-package\"\u003eThe 2025 Honda CR-V is a balanced package\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eStarting as low as $30,100, the 2025 Honda CR-V comes powered by a 190-horsepower turbocharged engine with standard front-wheel drive and available all-wheel drive. As far as efficiency goes, the standard gas-powered model is rated for 30 mpg in combined city/highway driving. \u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Honda CR-V Dream Pod Concept\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"5100\" height=\"3400\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODE0/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889814.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe Honda CR-V comes well-equipped for its price range, with a full suite of safety tech on the spec sheet. As far as infotainment goes, the base model features a seven-inch touchscreen display with Apple CarPlay and Android Auto compatibility. The EX-L trim adds a wireless phone charger to the list of standard equipment, making the CR-V more convenient for road trips.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe Japanese crossover is also available in a hybrid configuration that produces 204 horsepower. The Honda CR-V Hybrid earns up to 40 mpg combined, a 33% increase over the gas-only model. The range-topping Sport Touring Hybrid comes equipped with a 12-speaker Bose premium audio system complete with a subwoofer.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Honda CR-V Dream Pod Concept\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2720\" height=\"3400\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" sizes=\"(min-width: 750px) 750px, calc(100vw - 60px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODg5ODEx/cr-v-dream-pod-concept-889811.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eThe Honda CR-V Dream Pod concept is a practical idea, especially with van life’s popularity still going strong. At the end of the day, though, this is just an OEM take on a camper modification, with a combination of genuine accessories and aftermarket parts listed on the \u003ca href=\"https://www.honda.co.uk/cars/new/cr-v-hybrid-suv/dream-pod-concept.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003econcept’s official page\u003c/a\u003e. A camper conversion in our crossover won’t fly with two toddlers in tow, but if you’re looking for an adventure, transforming your vehicle into a camper is a great way to get started!\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003csection\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2026 Subaru Outback\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 24px), calc(100vw - 24px)\" srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_16,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 16w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_32,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_31.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODkwMDk4/2026_Subaru_Outback_3